Virtual Learning schedule will begin on September 18

post_text: Great information from our ELO Program!
shared_text:
YOUTUBE.COM
WHS ELO Information Webinar

WHS ELO Program is feeling excited.
August 26 at 9:24 AM ¬∑

Good news! If you couldn't attend Tuesday's ELO Information Webinar, here is the recording. In this 50 minute webinar we review what ELOs look like at Winnacunnet High School. It also details ELO requirements, how to request an ELO and changes to the program amid our pivot to Enriched Virtual Learning. You can also access the slideshow for this presentation in the details section of the video.

Extended Learning Opportunities (ELOs) are learning experiences that happen outside of the traditional classroom setting. These typically are things like career explorations, internships, independent studies, project based learning or even service aides (where a student helps a teacher in the classroom).

For more information please email Donna Couture, Director of Extended Learning at dcouture@warriors.winnacunnet.org

shared_text:
Winnacunnet High School Music Department
August 24 at 7:31 PM ¬∑

It was a great first day of masked, sanitized and socially distanced Band Camp!

It was a little rough at the start but it was great once things started going. Hearing music come out of WHS again was very exciting and such a sigh of relief!

The threat of severe thunderstorms brought us indoors for our full rehearsal. We are so thankful for the space we have so that we can spread ourselves out safely. Looking forward to the rest of the week!
